inkers on topics from education to ecology, this erudite but accessible book will be essential to anyone tackling the question of what it means to undertake critical and conceptually challenging fieldwork. Apprenticeship in Critical Ethnographic Practice explains how to seriously explore what it means to be human in a complex world—and why it is so important.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aApprenticeszLiberia. 0aEthnologyxResearchxMethodology. 0aEthnologyzLiberia. 0aGola (African people)xSocial life and customs. 0aTailorszLiberiaxApprentices. 0aTailorszLiberia. 0aVai (African people)xSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aGibson, Thomas P.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226470733423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226470733.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles